  <discussion>Kalmia polifolia is very closely related to K. microphylla and there is no general agreement on their taxonomic treatment.  The two taxa have different flavonoid profiles and are distinctly separated (S. Liu 1993).  The controversial Pacific lowland (Washington to Alaska) entity occidentalis resembles K. polifolia in structure; it is closely related to typical microphylla chemically and is separable from K. polifolia by key characters.</discussion>
